reviews_data.review_text: If I could give it a 10 I would. My friends and I spent an afternoon there making candles, bracelets, soups and soap. It truly was a fun day and they really make it an enjoyable experience.

I have shopped at The Merc since it open in 2018 and am always greeted with a smile and friendly hello. The unique and quirky items they sale are some of the best gifts I've given and received. Please support local. PS: I wish y'all still had the "naughty" room.

Absolutely adorable with so many surprises! My daughter and I came here for a mommy daughter gift swap and we selected the coolest things. The store flips periodically BUT, you can make soup, soap, candles, lotion, hats, body wash! It even has a small bar! It’s more of a general store with everything from pants and pots. Literally.

We’ll definitely be back!

Omg... such a nice location. I stopped in at jackass Cafe for a latte. The barrister was so friendly. This location has multiple businesses under one roof. I stopped in to make soap. This location is perfect for a date; you can make candles, soap, soup, and even flower arrangements.
Amazing atmosphere
Loved the atmosphere, staff, and all the DIY  bars.

My mom and I had the absolute best time there! Jen, in candle making was amazing and so much fun! Lots of fun things to make and take, sit down and enjoy a great lunch with a glass of wine. I highly recommend.
Wife's friend experienced racism here while ordering coffee during a pride event. Completely unacceptable.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello. Can you explain a bit more about this as we absolutely make no exceptions for and discrimination in our business and we are a very diverse company with diverse employees.

reviews_data.review_text: Coffee shop has racist employees. Would not serve my friend at pride event.

One year ago, on June 7, we were fortunate enough to host our Rehearsal Dinner at the Mercantile. Each and every person we worked with was incredibly helpful and kind. We could not have chosen a better location and would certainly recommend to others for your special events. The venue was gorgeous and accommodating to whatever style and vibe you wanted.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Happy Anniversary Ani! You were such a joy to work with and how beautiful your night was. Thank you for such a kind review and a happy walk down memory lane. -Brittany

reviews_data.review_text: The Mercantile was the perfect venue for our wedding and everyone here did an amazing job going above and beyond to make sure everything was perfect!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We thoroughly enjoyed celebrating your big day with you. Thank you for trusting our team with such a huge part of your life! Congratulations to you both!

reviews_data.review_text: Stopped in for a juice and to get some work done, Brittany was an absolute doll to my friend and I! Will definitely be back in the future!

Had a 10th birthday party for my daughter today and it was incredible!! I called literally two days ago when an issue arose with our original location & Ethan was phenomenal explaining all the different DIY bars they offer & helping me customize an option for a group of 10 year olds.

They were more than accommodating (especially for a last minute request!) HIGHLY recommend for a party, girls night, or any occasion! The DIY bars are so creative & fun. The girls had a blast making bracelets & hats & it was the perfect spot!

place is good food is good. currently training Athena my 3 month old GSD  for physctric service dog the staff behind the cafe are super friendly and adore her, i wouldn't recommend for dogs in training for service dogs, if you can find somewhere else for it, that place is good for socializing but not for service dog training got told politely by Stacy to move me and athena to the back of the restaurant twice this week. which i dont mind but honestly i was training so i left 2 times this week. other than that i recommend the chicken bacon ranch sandwich. i do like the candle bar made a candle there before  i started using it
Went for an event on nature preservation. Upstairs. Great venue for professional gatherings and catering.
Enjoyed
The scheduling of my event was easy and Brittany Kelly was right on point with everything. Great organizational skills.
Meh

I love the Mercantile. Visited today just because I had not been in a couple weeks. Constantly changing the merchandise and set up. I had a mocha latte' at the Jackass Cafe and wandered the store. Didn't buy anything else but had a refreshing break. The store adds so much to the downtown in Rockin' Hill.

I recently visited The Mercantile when I was in town visiting a friend on his recommendation (from my experience he has decided to quit going and he told me it wasn’t a surprise and the place has been going down hill fast with his recent interactions and conversations.) I love the art work of Shepard Fairy and it’s unfortunate he decided to put it in this particular business. I wanted to buy a beer, but there was no one to be found at the bar area for a very long time. I saw a tall thin man wearing glasses who seemed to be in charge putting something in a sink on the opposite side of what I guess is their bar. He looked me in the eyes but didn’t say anything and ignored me entirely. I gave up on waiting for someone to come around to serve me so I browsed and was shocked at the prices of the most simple items. Scratched up tiny furniture pieces for over $1000 dollars? Food items like canned tuna fish that were way out of date for $10-20 dollars? I don’t understand whatsoever how you think you’ll actually sell things at the insane prices you put on them. I always try to support small businesses wherever I go, but I would never come back to this place nor would I recommend it to anyone. I usually don’t even leave reviews, but I had to for this terrible experience. Good luck with whatever you are trying to accomplish here. This place is going to need all the luck they can get if that is what you call customer service.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your review. We’re so sorry your experience didn’t live up to your expectations. We hate to hear anyone have a less than 5 star service. You must have seen the bartender at the dish sink cleaning glasses, as it’s on the opposite side of the bar. Were you able to let any of the other team members know you wanted to order a drink? With us being a retail store, the bar is an extra added bonus we like to offer shoppers. And usually our retail staff tries to greet and welcome everyone, which is why you might not have been spoken to by the time you got to the back of the store. Our goal is that you’re hit several times before you even get close to the dish area. So terribly sorry if you weren’t greeted. We will have a talk with the team members. As for the tinned fish, it’s all the rage to create tinned fish boards now. The company we sell was on shark tank and has an incredible story that we support. Their tinned fish, selling at most $13.99 within our store, is fantastic and we sell often. None of which is out of date. The soonest expiring that we have checked is 2028, so I did want to clear that up as we take pride in checking the dates on any food we sell within the store. Our furniture pieces we sell are of great quality and/or amazing antique pieces. Within our store we have a cafe and deli, 5 different DIY bar options, a bar and an event space. All of which remain pretty busy for us during the season. We hope next time you visit, you’ll give us another chance. Thanks for the opportunity to improve.

reviews_data.review_text: I had an amazing time making my very first soup. Staff was very helpful and it’s really a cool place.
A cool place with several small businesses with cool items, some diy items like candle making and spice blending. A must visit in Rock Hill
I love the Mercantile!! staff is so friendly and eager to help, and there is so much to see and do! I love the DIY Bars, such a fun and unique concept!

Thank you, Thank YOU!!! Britany, Stacey, and the entire staff, you all are amazing! From greeting me, to personally assisting me, to making more products when I needed more…I can’t thank you all enough! Made it a one stop shop! And my whole team LOVED their unique gifts!!!

My SIL and I did a soap making - perfect fun.    Had a delicious coffee w hot soup and enjoyed poking about the place    We ll be back.    What a fun/unique place to visit w something different to share and do together.  Everyone there is so warm and friendly!  Thanks!

The owners and the staff are wonderful!  They are all very welcoming!  I feel at home when I am there!  Great products and great DIY projects.  The flowers are the best!  When I need a unique gift to give I always start at The Mercantile.
I love the staff here. They are very personable, kind, and helpful. The food, beverages, and products are great.

The Mercantile did the flowers and was the venue for my wedding reception on October 19th 2024.  They did an exceptional job.  The flowers were beautiful, the food was delicious and the staff went above and beyond to make our day special.

I love this store. They constantly change their inventory so there is always something to discover. My favorite place to find gifts or treat myself. Their cafe and fresh flowers are wonderful too! Best of all, the employees are always helpful and friendly. Highly recommend!!
Epic people, atmosphere, food and drinks. Good vibes. I was driving through and needed somewhere to stop. I feel so lucky to have stumbled on this place. A real gem. I’ll be back! Thanks 🙏
Lovely. Warm staff
Very nice setup. Lots of cool stuff and friendly staff. Will be doing more business with them.

A wonderful space for all! From the DIY bars, to the local artists & unique gifts to the cafe in the back; this The Mercantile has something for everyone! Staff is knowledgeable & kind. A great place to build community.

Perfect spot to grab breakfast, coffee, a cute gift or something for yourself, and even an event space. The team are all so welcoming and ready to help with your needs! Love the Mercs mission and how they are making Rock Hill a better place to live! 💗
Probably a nice place but they host events blasting music until 11 pm which isn’t very respectful to the surrounding community
What a fun place! Tons of variety and a bar! The DIY hat bar is so the best! Everyone was super nice. This will be a staple stop whenever we're in Rock Hill.
Great place. The people are so friendly. The flowers are exceptional!
Expensive gifts and not always family friendly.
Fascinating and eclectic store with a deli and bar to boot. Interesting mix of merchandise and very friendly staff. Definitely a great place to stop in and check out the vibe.
Love the variety of yummy pastries.
So much great stuff, fun craft opportunities, and the cafe and bar are fabulous! They even carry non-alcoholic beer!

I can not say enough great things about Katherine at the flower bar. Not only does she make the most fantastic wedding flower arrangements ever; she is also one of the most incredible people you will meet. So if you are ever in the area and just want to look at some amazing flower arrangements or meet a very cool person The Mercantile is the place you should stop.

You ever walk into someone’s living room while they had a family dinner ? And they did not know you at all and you were a foreign, unwelcome stranger……?

That’s how it felt walking into this store. Not only is it no welcoming to all, you feel like unless you have there beliefs or agree with there philosophy you’re not welcome.

I felt so uncomfortable coming here. And then the one worker who spoke was rude and her comments towards me were uncalled for, not friendly, and unwelcoming.

Only come here if you share their exact ideas. And their level of “open mind-ness”

The obsession with blasphemy is a bit weird, one of the shirts that they decide to put up on display the moment you walk in was distasteful. Weird to me when Buddha, allah, Mohammed, or any other religious figure is not joked about or put on display against their teachings. Just Jesus. How can you say you welcome all but so openly display someone’s religion in an incorrect way. I’m not in the business of shoving my religion down anyone’s throat, I happily walk into black owned, women owned, veteran owned, minority owned, lgbt owned stores with no hesitation. As long as I don’t feel unaccepted or threatened. And sadly as a minority, women, but one who just so happens to believe in Jesus, this store just made me uncomfortable. For the type of people to claim violence over anything, this stores displays and associated attitudes illicit violence. The store attendant even made a snarky comment about a street design shirt my sister wore (that happened to have a psalms verse printed on it). This is not very welcoming or accepting in my opinion. The store looks like it could’ve had potential to sell nice things but after that comment immediately upon entering, I just didn’t feel comfortable to look around to much.
Honestly walked in the wrong end of the building to get coffee 🤣 but I’m glad I did. This is a very cute eclectic store with several DIY stations.

There is no better place to get married, shop, eat and drink than this place! We had our wedding there this past weekend and I 1000% choose this place over and over again. Brittany and team went BEYOND with every singe detail and aspect of our big day. Brittany, Michael, LoLa, Katherine, Christan and everyone else....THANK YOU!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We were so honored to get to be apart of your big day! You were a gorgeous bride.We hope you’ll come visit us often ❤️ Thanks for being so amazing and trusting us with the details!

reviews_data.review_text:
This place is constantly changing around and upgrading! It's really worth checking out on and off or on a regular basis. For me personally it felt a bit like a boutique but now they've changed it a lot to where it's more of a hang out place with gifts and home goods to buy while you're there. The wine/beer bar is a great addition! I definitely feel like this is a place for people who have $ to spend to go out. If you don't want to spend any $ don't go in there. 😜  There's a high probability that you will want to purchase an item, a beverage or some food. And, now, you can purchase an experience. They set up tables for crafts and they provide the supplies. A really cool and fun new place to hang out.
A 3 star is mostly because many items and services that they offer are not "affordable" for my personal pocket. But overall I think for others, I've noticed that people send off a 4-5 *star vibe. I'm there often at the cafe/coffee shop, I love the vibe and the people. I'm so thrilled that they opened up the place for people to just hang there and offer us some fresh and quality food and drinks. They really are a special bunch and I'm grateful they are here.
This small city really needs a place like this! A local hang out spot with something for everyone. And, they're constantly evolving and thinking of new ideas on how to make things better.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Natalie, thanks so much for your sweet review! We’re so glad to have your support. We strive hard to offer a little something for everyone with our DIY bars starting at $4 with soap up to $25 with the hat bar, scattered with a bit of gifts in between and food and beverages! You hit the nail on the head…. we are trying to build a community hub here where everyone is welcome and all can hang out! Hope to see you again soon.

reviews_data.review_text: Great shop! I definitely recommend stopping in
A fantastic place! Coffee and tea is always good and it’s such a fun location. It always feels so good to shop local! Hoping for a location in Charlotte at some point.
There's a casual, comfortable atmosphere and the staff is great. Coffee is excellent, all the way from the drip to the lattes.

I rented the upstairs space of The Mercantile for my sister’s baby shower, and it could not have been more perfect! The space is eclectic and interesting and doesn’t need much at all in the way of decorating to be a stunning venue. Brittany was so kind and accommodating and responded to my (many) questions quickly. She was so helpful, sending me pictures as I live out of the area, showing some of my family the space so I could see it over FaceTime, and then allowed me to see upstairs when I randomly stopped by while in town. They have a ton of options as far as food, drinks, tables, decor, most anything you can’t think to throw a party; however, there is absolutely no pressure to use them if you have other vendors or prefer to DIY. If you’re looking for an incredible and unique venue in Rock Hill with the added benefit of supporting a local business that is doing great things for the local community, you’ve found the perfect place!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We were so honored to get to host your sister’s shower. You were such a joy to work with and we can’t thank you enough for supporting local, while being out of town! Cheers 🥂 Auntie!

Excellent event venue! Good food, good atmosphere.
Always a fun time!
What a great place!!  I loved my experience, especially with Kathryn and Mary !  Do miss Eloise.

The most beautiful shop! There is something for anyone and everyone and it’s hands down the best place to buy unique gifts. The cafe located inside has amazing coffee, drinks, and food, and the service is top notch. The atmosphere is warm and welcoming and the staff are always so nice and helpful. Amazing, beautiful, and welcoming environment with great staff!!
I love the vibe here! The staff are the friendliest around, and I loved the unique selection of gifts! I could spend hours in this store. I also recommend visiting the cafe in the back!
How could you not love this store?? They have everything!! The bring love and acceptance to everyone.

Mercantile is awesome, should always be on your lists of places to stop in at, especially on the weekends you're spending downtown Rock Hill! Lots of vendor setups, excellent food, coffee - friendly service!

reviews_data.review_text: The Mercantile suggests that the items sold are hand made and local but probably 98% of items are made in China, India and other places but not made locally! I ask one of the workers about wooden spoons, I was told they had and all I was finding were sets made in Chine. The worker showed me some cheap spoons from India and told me that not all their stuff was from China; they occasionally had stuff from as close as Tennessee but that they were waiting on a shipment to come in. BTW I saw the same holiday spatula's at Target being sold for $1.50. These were marked a lot more. The cup I bought last month for my sister for $15 I saw at Ross's for $5.50! Ridiculous! Don't tout that you are local and to buy local unless you do the same.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Shevawn thank you for your review. We are a locally owned gift store and furniture store. We do not suggest that all items items are handmade nor all local. We order from over hundreds of vendors which are all listed on our website. We are extremely community involved and use our profits to host many free events in our community as well as serve underserved communities and bring awareness to social injustice. We coach many local entrepreneurs, as well as sell many of their products from bath and body, spices, flowers, candles, stationary and more. We host monthly makers markets that consist of all local makers. I’m sorry that you feel you can get things cheaper at Target & Ross. Indeed you can as they are a large company that buys in bulk and get much better prices than a little ol store that is just buying for themselves. They also can afford to mark things down to meet their quotas. When you shop local, proceeds stay in the community. We employ 28 local Rock Hillians and each of those 28 employees shop and eat local. The impact is far greater than what you seem to understand. Many of the companies that we order from have far greater purposes and outreach programs. While many items are made in India, China and other countries, most of the companies we order from are Fair Trade. If you don’t think your low cost items from Target are coming from China too, then we have a problem. If the problem isn’t about origin and about costs then I’m sorry we aren’t a mass corporation that can get greater discounts. Otherwise, we will continue to be a pillar of hope, change and a source for amazing gifts and events! Have a great weekend.

Fabulous store and meeting place.

Workers seemed stressed/ understaffed especially young brunette, she had to ask for help upfront with two others there. Not sure, service was not genuinely warm. Smiles in showroom, but not cafe.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for leaving us such constructive feedback. We’re SO sorry the vibes were off and your drink was incorrect. This is my favorite local shop and where I always go to get unique, thoughtful, personal gifts. Went to the new location (finally!) today, in fact. As usual, everyone was friendly, helpful, caring, and just plain awesome! I love that this store is in our community and is supportive of ALL people, full stop. ♥️
Super friendly,  unique items and spacious.
I always find something to take home every time I come in — which is pretty often now with the cafe! The staff are wonderful and I especially love all the work the Mercantile does for the community!

Amazing environment, amazing staff, amazing owners, AMAZING store. Whether you looking to just go shopping, get some coffee, or just hang-out, this is the place to go. Rock Hill is so lucky that The Mercantile is apart of its’ community.

I wanted to buy a beer, but there was no one to be found at the bar area for a very long time. I saw a tall thin man wearing glasses who seemed to be in charge putting something in a sink on the opposite side of what I guess is their bar. He looked me in the eyes but didn’t say anything and ignored me entirely. I gave up on waiting for someone to come around to serve me so I browsed and was shocked at the prices of the most simple items. Scratched up tiny furniture pieces for over $1000 dollars? reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your review. We’re so sorry your experience didn’t live up to your expectations. We hate to hear anyone have a less than 5 star service. You must have seen the bartender at the dish sink cleaning glasses, as it’s on the opposite side of the bar. Were you able to let any of the other team members know you wanted to order a drink? With us being a retail store, the bar is an extra added bonus we like to offer shoppers. And usually our retail staff tries to greet and welcome everyone, which is why you might not have been spoken to by the time you got to the back of the store. Our goal is that you’re hit several times before you even get close to the dish area. So terribly sorry if you weren’t greeted. We will have a talk with the team members. As for the tinned fish, it’s all the rage to create tinned fish boards now. The company we sell was on shark tank and has an incredible story that we support. Their tinned fish, selling at most $13.99 within our store, is fantastic and we sell often. None of which is out of date. The soonest expiring that we have checked is 2028, so I did want to clear that up as we take pride in checking the dates on any food we sell within the store. Our furniture pieces we sell are of great quality and/or amazing antique pieces. Within our store we have a cafe and deli, 5 different DIY bar options, a bar and an event space. reviews_data.review_text: The Mercantile suggests that the items sold are hand made and local but probably 98% of items are made in China, India and other places but not made locally! I ask one of the workers about wooden spoons, I was told they had and all I was finding were sets made in Chine. The worker showed me some cheap spoons from India and told me that not all their stuff was from China; they occasionally had stuff from as close as Tennessee but that they were waiting on a shipment to come in. BTW I saw the same holiday spatula's at Target being sold for $1.50. These were marked a lot more. The cup I bought last month for my sister for $15 I saw at Ross's for $5.50! Ridiculous! Don't tout that you are local and to buy local unless you do the same.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Shevawn thank you for your review. We are a locally owned gift store and furniture store. We do not suggest that all items items are handmade nor all local. We order from over hundreds of vendors which are all listed on our website. We are extremely community involved and use our profits to host many free events in our community as well as serve underserved communities and bring awareness to social injustice. We coach many local entrepreneurs, as well as sell many of their products from bath and body, spices, flowers, candles, stationary and more. We host monthly makers markets that consist of all local makers. I’m sorry that you feel you can get things cheaper at Target & Ross. Indeed you can as they are a large company that buys in bulk and get much better prices than a little ol store that is just buying for themselves. They also can afford to mark things down to meet their quotas. When you shop local, proceeds stay in the community. We employ 28 local Rock Hillians and each of those 28 employees shop and eat local. The impact is far greater than what you seem to understand. Many of the companies that we order from have far greater purposes and outreach programs. While many items are made in India, China and other countries, most of the companies we order from are Fair Trade. If you don’t think your low cost items from Target are coming from China too, then we have a problem. If the problem isn’t about origin and about costs then I’m sorry we aren’t a mass corporation that can get greater discounts. Otherwise, we will continue to be a pillar of hope, change and a source for amazing gifts and events! Have a great weekend.
